<Author>amalitta
<Content>Reasonable  Went on a cruise end of February 2007 and it was in a decent location for leaving from the port (no, it is not directly across the street!), we rented a car, but they did have transportation going to the port for a fee. There is a Walgreens and a Publix nearby (within walking distance) to pick up anything that you may need for the kitchenette. It was what we expected for $100/night. The hotel was clean, staff was friendly and it was in a fairly safe area. One downfall - there isn't anywhere nearby to go out to eat, unless you have a car to go downtown or to South Beach. Regardless, we were pleased with our stay. 
